      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve written a &lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_Polish_notation&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;RPN&lt;/a&gt; string calculator in java, using TDD with these: mockito, hamcrest, junit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s close to the &lt;a href=&#34;http://osherove.com/tdd-kata-1/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;String Calculator kata&lt;/a&gt;, by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/RoyOsherove&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Roy Osherove&lt;/a&gt;. This RPN is using mocks (so more difficult than the String calculator)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve tried to practice &lt;a href=&#34;http://us2.campaign-archive1.com/?u=80ca60ec48ef77dfaa1f38943&amp;amp;id=42f9a0b66f&amp;amp;e=6ca6702beb&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Your tests are dragging you down&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/jbrains&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;J.B Rainsberger&lt;/a&gt; (mainly, to use something to write on). This behavior is also explained in the book &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.carlosble.com/libro-tdd/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Dirigido por tests&lt;/a&gt; (Spanish) by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/carlosble&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Carlos Bl√©&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My solution is &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/alvarogarcia7/kata-rpn-calculator-java&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Every step (red, green, refactor) has been saved.&lt;/p&gt;
